{{Mmgtable
|Activity = Completing [[The Hallowed Sepulchre|The Hallowed Sepulchre]]
|Image = [[File:Hallowed_Sepulchre_lobby.png|450px]]
|Skill =
* [[Sins of the Father]] quest requirements
* {{SCP|Agility|92}} to allow access to floor 5
* {{SCP|Thieving|66}}, {{SCP|Prayer|54}}, {{SCP|Construction|56}}, {{SCP|Ranged|62}} to complete skill challenges and loot coffins
|Item =
* [[Graceful outfit|Full graceful]], vampyre dust, a crossbow, mith grapple, planks/nails, 
* runes for an enchant spell, hammer, saw, [[strange old lockpick (full)|strange old lockpick]] or a normal lockpick, 
* prayer book or antipoison, stamina potion. Recommended to have purchased the [[hallowed grapple]], [[hallowed hammer]], 
* [[hallowed focus]], and [[hallowed symbol]] from the [[Mysterious Hallowed Goods|shop]].
|Quest = [[Sins of the Father]], optionally [[The Great Brain Robbery]] to use the [[prayer book]].
|Intensity = High
|Other = Patience when learning the floors

|Experience1 = Agility
|Experience1num = 12500
|Experience2 = Thieving
|Experience2num = 1200
|Experience3 = Prayer
|Experience3num = 200
|Experience4 = Magic
|Experience4num = 300
|Experience5 = Construction
|Experience5num = 1050

|isperkill = y
|kph = 6

|Input1 = Mahogany plank
|Input1num = 3
|Input2 = Rune nails
|Input2num = 7.5
|Input3 = Vampyre dust
|Input3num = 1
|Input4 = Stamina potion(4)
|Input4num = 0.25

<!--{{#vardefine:f2coffins|1}}
{{#vardefine:f3coffins|2}}-->
{{#vardefine:f4coffins|2}}
{{#vardefine:f5coffins|3}}
{{#vardefine:nummedcoffins|{{#expr:({{#var:f4coffins}})*.6 + ({{#var:f5coffins}})*.2}}}}
<!-- Extra two added bc the grand chest has 2 high rolls, but with no lockpick chance -->
{{#vardefine:numhighcoffins|{{#expr:({{#var:f4coffins}})*.4 + ({{#var:f5coffins}})*.8 + 2}}}}
{{#vardefine:solratef4|{{#expr:1/60}}}}
{{#vardefine:solratef5|{{#expr:1/40}}}}

<!-- Calculations for the average Coffin loot -->
{{#vardefine:HCLow|{{Average drop value|mob=Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)#Low|killname=loot|raw=y}}}}
{{#vardefine:HCMid|{{Average drop value|mob=Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)#Mid|killname=loot|raw=y}}}}
{{#vardefine:HCHigh|{{Average drop value|mob=Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)#High|killname=loot|raw=y}}}}
{{#vardefine:f2AveChest|{{GEP|Strange old lockpick (full)|1/120}}+119/120*(0.3 *{{#var:HCLow}}+0.6 *{{#var:HCMid}}+0.1 *{{#var:HCHigh}}) round 0}}
{{#vardefine:f3AveChest|{{GEP|Strange old lockpick (full)|1/90}} +  89/90*(0.15*{{#var:HCLow}}+0.65*{{#var:HCMid}}+0.2 *{{#var:HCHigh}}) round 0}}
{{#vardefine:f4AveChest|{{GEP|Strange old lockpick (full)|1/60}} +  59/60*(0.6 *{{#var:HCMid}}+0.4 *{{#var:HCHigh}}) round 0}}
{{#vardefine:f5AveChest|{{GEP|Strange old lockpick (full)|1/40}} +  39/40*(0.2 *{{#var:HCMid}}+0.8 *{{#var:HCHigh}}) round 0}}

<!-- Calculations for the average earnings from looting all chests from floors 2-5 -->
{{#vardefine:fullRun|{{#expr:({{#var:f2AveChest}})+({{#var:f2AveChest}})*2 + ({{#var:f4AveChest}})*2+({{#var:f5AveChest}})*5+({{GEP|Ring of endurance (uncharged)}})/200}} round 0}} 
{{#vardefine:finalOnlyRun|{{#expr:({{#var:f4AveChest}})*2+({{#var:f5AveChest}})*5+({{GEP|Ring of endurance (uncharged)}})/200}} round 0}}

<!-- As of an update on 23/09/20 100 marks can be exchanged for a Hallowed sack for an estimated value of 100,000 -->
|Output1 = Hallowed mark
|Output1num = {{#expr: ((3+6)/2 * 2) + ((4+6)/2 * 3) + (8+10) / 2}}
|Output1value = {{#expr: {{Average drop value|mob=Hallowed sack|raw=1}}/100}}

|Output2 = Ring of endurance (uncharged)
|Output2num = {{#expr:1 * (1/200)}}
|Output3 = Strange old lockpick (full)
|Output3num = {{#expr:{{#var:f4coffins}} * {{#var:solratef4}} + {{#var:f5coffins}} * {{#var:solratef5}}}}

<!-- Mid-Tier Loot -->
|Output4 = Adamant 2h sword
|Output4num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * 1 * (1/10)}}
|Output5 = Adamant platebody
|Output5num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * 1 * (1/10)}}
|Output6 = Cosmic rune
|Output6num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (60+100)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output7 = Death rune
|Output7num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (60+100)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output8 = Nature rune
|Output8num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (60+100)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output9 = Adamant bolts
|Output9num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (50+200)/2 * (1/10)}}
<!-- Monkfish are also rolled on the high tier table -->
|Output10 = Monkfish
|Output10num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (1+3)/2 * (1/10) + {{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (2+6)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output11 = Prayer potion(4)
|Output11num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * 1 * (1/10)}}
|Output12 = Ranarr weed
|Output12num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (1+2)/2 * (1/10)}}
<!-- Coins are also rolled on the high tier table -->
|Output13 = Coins
|Output13num = {{#expr:{{#var:nummedcoffins}} * (7500+12500)/2 * (1/10) + {{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (17500+25000)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output13value = 1

<!-- High-Tier Loot -->
|Output14 = Rune 2h sword
|Output14num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * 1 * (1/10)}}
|Output15 = Rune platebody
|Output15num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * 1 * (1/10)}}
|Output16 = Law rune
|Output16num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (150+250)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output17 = Blood rune
|Output17num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (150+250)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output18 = Soul rune
|Output18num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (150+250)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output19 = Runite bolts
|Output19num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (100+300)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output20 = Sanfew serum(4)
|Output20num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (1+2)/2 * (1/10)}}
|Output21 = Ranarr seed
|Output21num = {{#expr:{{#var:numhighcoffins}} * (1+2)/2 * (1/10)}}

|Location = [[Darkmeyer]]
|Category = Skilling
|SkillCategory = Agility
|Members = Yes
|Details = 
{{*}} Assumes the player is looting all chests on floors 4 and 5, using Lvl-3 Enchant, mahogany planks, and a [[hallowed hammer]], [[hallowed focus]], and [[hallowed symbol]]. Looting all chests on floors 4 and 5 requires near click-perfect execution and all mentioned hallowed items. If the player is still learning floor 5 or is not yet click perfect, a [[hallowed token]] (worth 10 [[hallowed mark]]s) can be used to grant 1 extra minute of time. This will decrease profitability by {{Coins|{{Average drop value|mob=Hallowed sack|raw=1}}/10 round 0}} per token (likely one per run).

The [[Hallowed Sepulchre]] is a solo [[Agility]] activity in [[Darkmeyer]] in which the player avoids obstacles to reach the [[Grand Hallowed Coffin]] and loot other [[Coffin (Hallowed Sepulchre)|coffins]] before time runs out. The activity becomes highly profitable at 92 agility, as this allows players to loot floor 5, where the [[ring of endurance (uncharged)|ring of endurance]] can be obtained. Due to the high proportion of profit allocated to the ring drop, actual profit will be influenced largely by player luck. Other notable frequent high-value drops are ranarr seeds, sanfew serums, runite bolts, and blood runes.

{{*}} Once comfortable with the final floors a [[hallowed token]] can be used to ensure the player can loot all chests on floors 2 and 3 in addition to 4 and 5. It is recommended to bring three [[vampyre dust]] per run and 6 [[mahogany plank]]s. If click perfect, this can be achieved without a [[hallowed token]]. 

{{*}} Looting all chests from floors 2-5 (including the [[Grand Hallowed Coffin]]) without a token will yield an average of {{coins|{{#var:fullRun}}}} per run including the [[Ring of endurance]] and {{coins|{{#expr:({{#var:fullRun}})*1-({{GEP|Ring of endurance (uncharged)|1/200}}) round 0}}}} without the [[Ring of endurance]]. This is compared against an average of {{coins|{{#var:finalOnlyRun}}}} per run including the [[Ring of endurance]] and {{coins|{{#expr:({{#var:finalOnlyRun}})*1-({{GEP|Ring of endurance (uncharged)|1/200}}) round 0}}}} without the [[Ring of endurance]] for completing just floors 4 and 5 [an increase of {{coins|{{#expr:({{#var:fullRun}})-({{#var:finalOnlyRun}})}}}}/run or approximately {{coins|{{#expr:(({{#var:fullRun}})-({{#var:finalOnlyRun}}))*6}}}}/hr at 6 laps per hour].

Note that if the player is planning on training [[Construction]] using mahogany planks normally, it is recommended to continue using them here as the gp/xp of using the planks to [[Bridge (Hallowed Sepulchre)|repair bridges]] is superior to using them normally.

}}
